description:
President Donald Trump hailed a productive meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in Florida today, while saying disagreements remain over the West Bank. Trump said Hamas “will be given a very short period of time” to disarm to move to the second phase of his Gaza peace plan and that Israel has “100%” lived up to the plan.

CNN's Jim Sciutto discusses with his "The Arena" panel.

8:05 Former Biden White House director of message planning Meghan Hays on the state of the relationship between Trump and Netanyahu 
#Trump #Netanyahu #News
title: Trump and Netanyahu hail 'productive' meeting
